<div id="review_1949489192" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1949489192" />
    <a title="Oliviu Crâznic" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5613774-oliviu-cr-znic"><img alt="Oliviu Crâznic" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1307829345p2/5613774.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1949489192?book_show_action=true">Mar 22, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Oliviu Crâznic" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Oliviu Crâznic" href="/user/show/5613774-oliviu-cr-znic">Oliviu Crâznic</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1949489192" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16752097647863050154">Excellent writing and a very promising beginning - quickly enough ruined (totally!) by a major disappointment: the educated girl finds a burglar in her home and... invites him to bed her?! <br/>I could not read more; it may happen in the real life, I admit (people are strange and often enough, quite insane and depraved, we already know that): but this is no valid reason to read about it.<br/>At least, not for me.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


